def se(img,fwhm):
    
    img_name = img.split('.fits')[0].split('fits/')[1]
    
    cmd1 = 'sex -c ../default_files/default.sex -PARAMETERS_NAME ../default_files/default.param.ape -DETECT_THRESH %s -ANALYSIS_THRESH %s -PHOT_APERTURES \
                %1.2f -CATALOG_TYPE ASCII_HEAD -CATALOG_NAME %s.cat %s,%s' %(detect_tresh,analysis_tresh,1.5*fwhm,img_name,reference_image,img)
    os.system('%s' %cmd1);
    os.system('mv %s.cat slice_catalogs/' %img_name)

    pass

In [9]:
N = 3721
CRPIX1 = 1.
CRDEL1 = 1.25
CRVAL1 = 4699.25

def wl(spec_size=np.arange(N), crpix=CRPIX1, crdelt=CRDEL1, crval=CRVAL1):
    """
    N: numero del slice
    crpix: reference slice de inicio
    crdelt: delta lambda por cada slice
    crval: lambda de referencia/inicio
    """
    return (spec_size+1-crpix)*crdelt + crval
#(3721)*1.25+4699.625

    return 8542. * (rv / c.to('km/s').value)

rv1 = np.empty(norm_spec.shape[0])
rv2 = np.empty(norm_spec.shape[0])
rv3 = np.empty(norm_spec.shape[0])
rv4 = np.empty(norm_spec.shape[0])
rv5 = np.empty(norm_spec.shape[0])
rv6 = np.empty(norm_spec.shape[0])

def many_RV(n, spec):
    
    rad_vel, cc = CC(w, spec, template1.aa.values, template1.flux.values, rvmin=-250., rvmax=250., drv=1., skipedge=100)
    rv1[n] = rad_vel[np.argmax(cc)]
    rad_vel, cc = CC(w, spec, template2.aa.values, template2.flux.values, rvmin=-250., rvmax=250., drv=1., skipedge=100)
    rv2[n] = rad_vel[np.argmax(cc)]

    rad_vel, cc = CC(w, spec, template3.aa.values, template3.flux.values, rvmin=-250., rvmax=250., drv=1., skipedge=100)
    rv3[n] = rad_vel[np.argmax(cc)]
    rad_vel, cc = CC(w, spec, template4.aa.values, template4.flux.values, rvmin=-250., rvmax=250., drv=1., skipedge=100)
    rv4[n] = rad_vel[np.argmax(cc)]

    rad_vel, cc = CC(w, spec, template5.aa.values, template5.flux.values, rvmin=-250., rvmax=250., drv=1., skipedge=100)
    rv5[n] = rad_vel[np.argmax(cc)]
    rad_vel, cc = CC(w, spec, template6.aa.values, template6.flux.values, rvmin=-250., rvmax=250., drv=1., skipedge=100)
    rv6[n] = rad_vel[np.argmax(cc)]

    pass
